10. Failure Handling

Scenario| Handling
Current config extraction failed| Log parsing failure
Previous config missing| Mark comparison incomplete
Config normalization failed| Raise comparison error
Duplicate comparison request| Deduplication handling
Repository unavailable| Retry with backoff

---

11. Scalability Considerations

- Comparison processing should be asynchronous
- Comparison services should support parallel execution
- Large configuration payloads should support optimized parsing
- Drift processing should support horizontal scaling

---

12. Security Considerations

- Configuration data should be securely stored
- Sensitive configuration fields may be masked
- Comparison results must be audit traceable
- Access to configuration repository should be restricted

---

13. Assumptions

- Current configuration payload is available through event pipeline
- Previously applied configuration is stored in SDN repository
- Config normalization rules are supported
- Syslog event ingestion framework already exists

